name: Google Cloud SDK
desc: Set of tools to manage resources and applications hosted on Google Cloud
caveats:
google-cloud-sdk is installed at $(brew --prefix)/Caskroom/google-cloud-sdk/latest/google-cloud-sdk. Add your profile:

  for bash users
    export CLOUDSDK_PYTHON="$(brew --prefix)/opt/python@3.8/libexec/bin/python"
    source "$(brew --prefix)/Caskroom/google-cloud-sdk/latest/google-cloud-sdk/path.bash.inc"
    source "$(brew --prefix)/Caskroom/google-cloud-sdk/latest/google-cloud-sdk/completion.bash.inc"

  for zsh users
    export CLOUDSDK_PYTHON="$(brew --prefix)/opt/python@3.8/libexec/bin/python"
    source "$(brew --prefix)/Caskroom/google-cloud-sdk/latest/google-cloud-sdk/path.zsh.inc"
    source "$(brew --prefix)/Caskroom/google-cloud-sdk/latest/google-cloud-sdk/completion.zsh.inc"

  for fish users
    set -g -x "CLOUDSDK_PYTHON" "$(brew --prefix)/opt/python@3.8/libexec/bin/python"
    set -g fish_user_paths "$(brew --prefix)/Caskroom/google-cloud-sdk/latest/google-cloud-sdk/path.fish.inc" $fish_user_paths
